#X text 358 97 NOTE:;
#X text 358 115 This abstraction only emulates what can be done with
a proper external. It stores the state of all jack connections internally
in a cache \, which is updated with the 'refresh' method. Any modifications
on the connections are immediately applied to the cache and then to
the reald world with 'jack_connect' and 'jack_disconnect' commands.
This allows the abstraction to handle any requests immediately (synchronosously
\, in zero logical time). However \, external modifications won't be
detected. This can cause errors which are reported on the right outlet.
If such errors occur \, it is adviced to 'refresh' the cache again
to make sure that the internal cache reflects the actual connections.
;
